<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 25.920000000000073pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;text-align: justify;margin-top:13.44pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6.3 You agree that AT TABLE shall under no circumstance be held responsible or liable for any representation in AT TABLE Invitations or for AT TABLE Events not running smoothly or as advertised or otherwise being unsatisfactory.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 21.840000000000032pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:13.2pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">6.4 In certain circumstances, AT TABLE may decide, in its sole discretion, that it is necessary or desirable to cancel AT TABLE Events. In these circumstances AT TABLE may determine, in its sole discretion, to refund to the Diner part or all of the amounts charged to the Diners. You agree that AT TABLE and the relevant Diners or Chefs will have no liability to you in respect of such cancellations or refunds.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 333.12pt;margin-top:22.32pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7. Financial arrangements&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:9.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7.1 When issuing AT TABLE Invitations, Chefs state the fees that they will charge each Diners, these fees are quoted inclusive of all sales and analogous or other taxes (the “Chef’s Charges”). AT TABLE arranges a service for these fees to be collected and held in a third-party trust account on terms that the funds will be paid in accordance with these T&amp;Cs (arranging this collection and holding service constitutes a part of the AT TABLE Services). AT TABLE may charge Diners a fee for the use of the AT TABLE Services (the “AT TABLE Fees”). Acceptance of a AT TABLE Invitation constitutes agreement to pay the Chef’s Charges and any AT TABLE Fees (the “Transaction Fees”). The total amount of the Transaction Fees is the amount payable by the Diners in respect of each AT TABLE Invitations at the time that the Diners accepts the AT TABLE Invitations.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 21.36000000000007pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:12.48pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7.2 Where applicable, the AT TABLE Fees are calculated as a variable percentage of the Chef’s Charges. Any AT TABLE Fees are payable by the Diners at the same time as payment of the Chef’s Charges. To the extent that the AT TABLE Fees are subject to sales taxes, such as VAT, these taxes will be included in the total amount payable by the Diner in respect of the Transaction Fees. Where AT TABLE charges AT TABLE Fees it shall on request provide an invoice in respect of those AT TABLE Fees, separately identifying any sales taxes charged by AT TABLE.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 30.240000000000066pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:13.44pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7.3 Chefs agree and acknowledge that they are responsible for discharging all of their own tax obligations (including sales taxes including, but not limited to, VAT) whether these are imposed on a state, local or other level. AT TABLE assumes no obligations whatsoever in this regard. In particular, AT TABLE assumes no responsibility (actual or deemed) to notify or explain to Chefs, or to enquire into, the VAT or sales taxes treatment of any Chefs or AT TABLE Events.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 24.000000000000057pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:13.44pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7.4 If AT TABLE so requires for the purposes of its dealings with any tax or regulatory authority, Chefs and Diners shall provide to AT TABLE, promptly on request, any information, data, documentation and/or copies of communications (whether in electronic format or otherwise) which relate to AT TABLE Events in which they have participated. Chefs shall, promptly on request, provide to AT TABLE all reasonable assistance in any discussion or dispute with any tax authority with respect to the VAT or sales tax treatment of AT TABLE Events in which those Chefs have participated. Each Chefs agrees to indemnify AT TABLE for any VAT or any tax obligations which AT TABLE is required to pay and which arise wholly from AT TABLE Events hosted by that Chefs.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 45.12000000000006pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:13.44pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7.5 You may only make payments in respect of AT TABLE Invitations through the payment processing facilities provided on the AT TABLE Websites, by special arrangement with AT TABLE through its direct booking services or of through a third-party agency that is authorised by AT TABLE to provide those parts of the AT TABLE Services relating to processing payments. Please check with AT TABLE to ensure that any third-party with whom you are dealing is properly authorised by AT TABLE. If the AT TABLE Invitations is transacted through an authorised third- party you may not be required to pay any AT TABLE Fees, but the authorised third-party agent may instead charge an administration fee.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 36.00000000000006pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:13.44pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7.6 You agree that the sole and exclusive role and responsibility of AT TABLE (and any of its authorised third-party agents) in providing AT TABLE Services relating to processing payments is to arrange the collection of payments from Diners and for the payment of the amounts collected in accordance with these T&amp;Cs (and you agree that they have no other or further liability to you in respect of any payment made).&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 23.28000000000003pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:13.44pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">7.7 Payments are made by Diners through selected payment providers. The terms on which the payment providers hold funds are stated in their terms. AT TABLE may receive amounts due to Chefs from payment providers, where it does so such funds will be held in AT TABLE’s bank account until they are transferred to the Chefs (or, where appropriate, reimbursed to the Diners).&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 240.24000000000007pt;margin-top:22.32pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-weight: 700; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">8. Insurance, disputes, resolution and refunds&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 11.040000000000077pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:9.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">8.1&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Diners may need to cancel a AT TABLE Invitations that they have previously accepted, in such cases please follow the instructions as described in AT TABLE Websites. Diners shall qualify for a full refund of the Chef’s Charges if (a) the Diners notifies AT TABLE of cancellation during usual business hours (being 9am to 5pm on weekdays other than public holidays) or by hours as stated in the AT TABLE’s Cancellation Policy, or (b) if the Chefs cancels the AT TABLE Events for any reason.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 34.80000000000007pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:12.48pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">8.2&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">In case things go wrong and if a Diners believes that the Chefs failed to fulfill an essential obligation of the AT TABLE Events then the Diners may until midnight on the day following the date on which the relevant AT TABLE Events was conducted request that the whole or a part of the payment is refunded by sending an email to contact@attable.co specifying the AT TABLE Events reference, identifying the Chefs, specifying the amount of the Transaction Fees, saying how much the Diners wishes to be reimbursed and giving as much information as possible in relation to the problem/ relevant failures/ reasons for believing that payment should be refunded. AT TABLE reserves the right to deliberate on the amount (if any) to be refunded.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 15.840000000000032pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:13.44pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">8.3&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">AT TABLE intends to give the benefits and protections to all Chefs and Diners participates AT TABLE Events by providing AT TABLE’s insurance policy. Please notify AT TABLE immediately at contact@attable.co if you have suffered loss which appears to be covered by our insurance policy. The notification should include all relevant details and include such information and evidence as is available to you to substantiate the claim. By sending the email you agree to provide us with all further information that is reasonably available to you which we request in relation to the claim, including any medical or travel details and expenses, details of any other insurance available to you and any proposed or agreed resolution of any of the circumstances relating to the claim with any third party. AT TABLE agrees to indemnify or compensate you in respect of any such losses to the extent only that it is able to secure recovery, if any, from its insurance policy. AT TABLE will not deduct any administration fees from any such amount so recovered. Save as provided in this clause 8.3, AT TABLE has no further or other obligation or liability in respect of its guarantee.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 21.840000000000032pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:12.48pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(89, 89, 89); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">8.4&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 9.7444pt; font-family: Arial; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">If you have a dispute relating to a AT TABLE Events, we encourage you (although this is not compulsory) to contact us at contact@attable.co in order to try to resolve the dispute amicably.&nbsp;</span></p>
