<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 93.12000000000006pt;margin-top:12.48pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">When you check the box at the end of this Diner’s charter to show your acceptance:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 11.040000000000077pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">– You are agreeing to be bound to the Diner’s Charter which forms a contract between yourself and AT TABLE (hereinafter referred to as the “Diner’s Charter”); and – You are expressly renewing your acceptance to be bound by the T&amp;Cs.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 14.400000000000034pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">We would advise you to read through the T&amp;Cs again. The T&amp;Cs and the Diner’s Charter form a contractual whole by which you are bound when you use the AT TABLE Website as a “Diners” (as this term is defined in the T&amp;Cs). In the event of contradiction between a stipulation in the T&amp;Cs and a stipulation in the Diner’s Charter, the stipulation in the Diner’s Charter shall prevail.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 36.960000000000036pt;margin-top:12.48pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">If you do not agree to be bound by the Diner’s Charter, you are not allowed to use the AT TABLE Websites as a Diner.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 304.56000000000006pt;margin-top:12.48pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">2. Purpose of the Chef’s Charter&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 15.120000000000061pt;margin-top:9.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">The Diner’s Charter aims to regulate your rights and obligations more specifically in the event that you should decide to use the AT TABLE Services (as the term is defined in the T&amp;Cs) as a Diners.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 255.60000000000002pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">3. The Possession of a AT TABLE Account&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 1.6800000000000637pt;margin-top:9.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">To become a Diner, you must first create a “AT TABLE Account” (as the term is defined in the T&amp;Cs) and complete it by providing, as a minimum, the following obligatory information:&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 8.159999999999997pt;margin-right: 261.36000000000007pt;margin-top:15.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">-&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">your first name and last name,&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 8.159999999999997pt;margin-right: 261.36000000000007pt;margin-top:15.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">-&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">your mobile phone number,&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 8.159999999999997pt;margin-right: 261.36000000000007pt;margin-top:15.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">-&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">your email address, and&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 8.159999999999997pt;margin-right: 261.36000000000007pt;margin-top:15.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:'Times New Roman';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">-&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">your most updated profile photograph.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-right: 0.28346456692915467pt;margin-top:15.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">You are committed to providing an updated profile photograph that represents you to the exclusion of any other person and/or work. By uploading such a photograph, you guarantee to AT TABLE that this does not infringe any intellectual property rights belonging to a third party and that you expressly authorize AT TABLE to use your image, and that you grant it a license for use under the conditions set out in the T&amp;Cs. You are solely liable for any claim and / or charge made by a third party for the photo or image uploaded, and warrant that you shall use your best efforts to render AT TABLE not liable for any civil claim(s) and / or criminal offense(s), including being responsible for all related expenses thereto. You are committed to provide full, exact and honest information and to keep it permanently updated.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 255.36000000000007pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">4. The AT TABLE Invitations offered to you&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 4.080000000000041pt;margin-top:9.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">AT TABLE Invitations (as the term is defined in the T&amp;Cs) that are published on the AT TABLE Websites are defined and offered by the “Chefs” (as the term is defined in the T&amp;Cs). Before accepting a AT TABLE Invitations, you must read this charter in detail. Do not accept any AT TABLE Invitations if you have any doubts or questions in your mind.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 310.80000000000007pt;margin-top:15.12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">5. Your obligations as a Diners&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: -0.4799999999999045pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:18.72pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">5.1. Principles of openness, respect, tolerance and non-discrimination&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">Via AT TABLE Services you can visit a Chef’s premise, possibly in the presence of other Diners. You agree to respect your Chefs and the other Diners, as well as their respective cultures, and to treat them in a non-discriminatory manner. You agree to abide by your Chefs’ household rules, such as removing your shoes in particular, when asked to do so by your Chefs. This list is not exhaustive but under no circumstances should these rules infringe your modesty or integrity.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 73.68000000000006pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:18.72pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">5.2. Your obligation to respect the hospitality offered to you&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">The most important quality in a Diners is to respect the hospitality offered by their Chefs.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 24.000000000000057pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">You agree not to enter any part of their premises other than that shown to you by your Chefs, and in particular not to enter any room without prior invitation from your Chefs.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: -0.4799999999999045pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">You agree not to interfere with your Chefs’ property, in particular their personal items, and not to move any object without prior invitation from your Chefs. You agree to accept and respect the presence of other people in the premises, including but not limited to family members and/or friends of your Chefs.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 27.840000000000032pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">You agree not to damage either the premises to which your Chefs has invited you, nor the building, furniture in or around the premises.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:18.72pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">5.3. Your acceptance of the event you booked&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">You agree to give your Chefs prior notice, when you accept a AT TABLE Invitations, in an exhaustive and truthful manner, of any foods or drinks to which you may be allergic and/or that you may refuse to eat or drink for whatever reason (reasons that you are not obliged to justify). You agree not to accept a AT TABLE Invitations without obtaining prior confirmation from your Chefs that their food is free from such foods and/or drinks. In the event that you should accept a AT TABLE Invitations without having obtained prior confirmation from your Chefs, or in the knowledge of the presence in the composition of the meals offered of one or several of these foods and/or drinks, then the amount requested by the Chefs and our commission, including tax, shall remain payable. You cannot ask for a dish to be replaced by another and you will eat and drink the food and drinks offered to you at your own risk. You guarantee to us on this matter that we cannot be held in any way responsible in such a circumstance.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 5.5200000000000955pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:33.120000000000005pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">5.4. Your obligation to leave your Chefs once the invitation and food experience are finished&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">The invitation and food experience must definitely last no longer than four hours. We automatically and without discrimination refuse any AT TABLE Invitations of an estimated duration superior to four hours. You agree to leave the premises at the request of your Chefs and in all cases upon expiry of the maximum duration estimated by the AT TABLE Invitations as stated by the Chefs on the AT TABLE Websites. Under no circumstances shall we be held responsible in the event that you do not respect this obligation. You agree to take personal responsibility in the event of a claim by a third party or by your Chefs in the event that you do not respect this obligation. You also guarantee us against any claim by a third party or by your Chefs in this respect.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 8.160000000000082pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:18.72pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">5.5. Respect for neighbors and other members of your Chef’s household&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">You agree to respect your Chef’s neighbors and not to behave in such a way that may cause any nuisance, particularly noise, to be suffered by neighbors in the course of a AT TABLE Invitations. Under no circumstances shall we be held responsible in the event that you do not respect this obligation. You agree to take personal responsibility in the event of a claim by a third party in the event that you do not respect this obligation. You also guarantee us against any claim by a third party in this respect.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 13.440000000000055pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:18.96pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">5.6. Respect for the contract to which you are agreeing&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">The definition and publication on the AT TABLE Websites of a AT TABLE Invitations constitutes a pre- contractual offer. If you are interested in a AT TABLE Invitations offer presented by the Chefs, you can book the AT TABLE Invitations. In the event that you successfully booked the AT TABLE Invitations, the pre-contractual offer shall become a contractual offer (hereinafter referred to as the “Diner-Chef Contract” The Diner-Chef Contract is made between the Chef and yourself, to the exclusion of AT TABLE.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 3.3600000000000136pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">The terms and conditions of this Diner-Chef Contract are constituted by the terms and conditions defined in said AT TABLE Invitations as well as, where applicable, the terms of any agreements that you may have made during direct exchanges with the Chefs, whether these agreements were made via the AT TABLE websites or not.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 133.68000000000006pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">You agree to respect the terms and conditions of this Diner-Chef Contract.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 1.2000000000000455pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">In the event that you do not attend the AT TABLE Invitations at the time and date agreed, the total amount payable by the Diners, as well as our commission, including tax, shall remain payable by yourself and shall be paid to your Chefs and to AT TABLE.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 5.759999999999991pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">In the event of any dispute between you and your Chefs due to a failure by one of these parties to honor their contractual obligations, AT TABLE shall in no way be held responsible.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: -1.9200000000000017pt;margin-right: 0.7200000000000273pt;margin-top:14.88pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">In the unlikely event that the responsibility of AT TABLE should be called into question by your Chefs, or by one or several of the other Diners, or by a third party due to your failure to respect the Diner-Chef Contract, you agree to compensate AT TABLE for any damage that it may suffer as a result (damage to the company image, economic damage, lawyer fee, court fee etc.). You agree to endeavor to hold AT TABLE harmless, exonerate AT TABLE, hold AT TABLE not liable for any civil liability or criminal offense.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-left: 34.08pt;margin-right: 11.760000000000048pt;text-indent: 1.9200000000000017pt;margin-top:18.96pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">5.7. Respect for the regulations that apply to you&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">We advise you to make yourself familiar with the regulations, whether fiscal, administrative, or of any other nature, that may apply to you. You agree, where applicable, to respect any regulations governing the premises where a AT TABLE Invitations takes place.&nbsp;</span></p>
<p dir="ltr" style="line-height:1.38;margin-right: -2.159999999999968pt;margin-top:16.08pt;margin-bottom:0pt;"><span style="font-size:9.744400024414062pt;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:700;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;">6. Responsibility – Insurance&nbsp;</span></p>
